01/12/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Bosiljka Mladic is scheduled to go on trial in Belgrade on Friday (December 3rd), media reported on Wednesday. 
The wife of fugitive former Bosnian Serb commander Ratko Mladic is charged with illegal arms possession. 
The guns, an automatic weapon, a hunting rifle and several pistols, were seized during a December 2008 raid on the family home in Belgrade. 
If convicted, she could face up to ten years in prison. 
(Tanjug, B92 - 01/12/10)
